ion","Capacitation","Spermiogenesis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpermiation\u003C/strong\u003E is the release of mature sperm from Sertoli cells into the lumen of seminiferous tubules. \u003Cstrong\u003EEjaculation\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the expulsion of semen from the penis. \u003Cstrong\u003EEmission\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the movement of sperm into the urethra. \u003Cstrong\u003ECapacitation\u003C/strong\u003E is the final maturation process that occurs in the female reproductive tract, involving membrane changes that enable sperm to undergo the acrosome reaction and penetrate the zona pellucida. \u003Cstrong\u003ESpermiogenesis\u003C/strong\u003E is the process where spermatids mature into spermatozoa.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Capacitation is the final maturation process that sperm must undergo in the female reproductive tract to gain fertilising capability.","Capacitation involves biochemical changes that enable sperm to undergo the acrosome reaction and penetrate the zona pellucida."],"references":["O\u0027Donnell L, Nicholls PK, O\u0027Bryan MK, McLachlan RI, Stanton PG. Spermiation: The process of sperm release. Spermatogenesis. 2011 Jan;1(1):14-35. doi: 10.4161/spmg.1.1.14525. PMID: 21866274; PMCID: PMC3158646","Griswold MD. Spermatogenesis: The Commitment to Meiosis. Physiol Rev. 2016 Jan;96(1):1-17. doi: 10.1152/physrev.00013.2015. PMID: 26537427; PMCID: PMC4698398","Chu DS, Shakes DC. Spermatogenesis. Adv Exp Med Biol. 2013;757:171-203. doi: 10.1007/978-1-4614-4015-4_7. PMID: 22872478; PMCID: PMC9217098"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56970"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15798"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56970","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56970"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-18T